resources.name: Sign Token
resources.description:
## The CORSIGN Model
The corsign model and the encryption implementation is published open source at https://github.com/innFactory/corsign-core

### CORSIGN Model

Minimum required fields for local check in are firstame, lastname, birthday, email and/or phone and the test result as isNegative true or false.

if the test is positive the health authority needs more information about the person like sex, street1/street2, zip, city

```
{
  "sub": "UUID (Unique User IDentifier) which could be used in third-party applications such as SORMAS, valid until a new test is performed",
  "exp": "The token expires after a pre-defined duration (e.g 24 hours) passed since the Sars-CoV-2 was done",
  "iat": "Date and time of the Sars-Cov-2 test",
  "nbf": "Valid not before Sars-Cov-2 test date and time",
  "aud": "Place for the signer, can be used to store additional information for a third-party application",
  "pld": {
    "person": {
      "idCardNumber": "LFC123ABC",
      "firstname": "Max *required",
      "lastname": "Mustermann *required",
      "sex": "F(emale)|M(ale)|D(ivers)",
      "birthdate": "timestamp in milliseconds",
      "email": "meine@mail.de *required or phoneNumber", 
      "phoneNumber": "0803199999 *required or E-Mail",
      "street1": "BahnhofstraÃŸe 1",
      "street2": "",
      "city": "Rosenheim",
      "zip": "zip code",
      "country": "2 letter Alpha-2 country code as defined in ISO 3166"
    },
    "information": {
      "isNegative": true,
      "testType": "Type of test used e.g. pcr|antigen|...",
      "testId": "Barcode of Covid19 Test",
      "isVaccinated": true,
      "vaccine": "Shortname of the administered vaccine like BNT162b2|mRNA-1273|...",
      "appData1": "Additional third-party app data as json",
      "appData2": "Additional third-party app data as json"
    }
  }
}
```

## Issuer
Issuer is https://iss.corsign.de and the validation ui runs at https://www.corsign.de/v1/validate/:jwt. You should prepand this, if you use generate your own QR Code from the JWT token. With this prefix every smartphone qr scanner is able to validate the token without an app. For your validation you have to split the url after /validation/

## Query Parameter

- withQR=true|false => generate the QR Code 
- sendEmail=true|false => Send Mail to the email signed inside the JWT.

## Response Body
The value contains the corsign model. The qr field contains a base64 encoded png containing the validation ui plus token. For example https://corsign.de/v1/validate/:JWT. If requireManualSendOfPositive is true, you must transmit your positive cases to your health authority by yourself. Info tells you why. The token also send out to the email contact signed inside of the token. if the send is successfull emailSendSuccessful will be true.
```
{
  "value": "eyJraWQiOiI2MzMxZTQ4NC01ZjFlLTQ2OTktYTUyMS0xZjBjYWI0MzFmZjMiLCJhbGciOiJSUzUxMiJ9..eMphuY_AOnrMCzCKszKsUQuaLXUhL3HuhlSI9FhGAP27S4VD8jb4Mthzj6QOmqKszJRdBBup-GnON1qpVfBdVHCWS33j_AyoLY90RZC5EGY0dWySW8bi5YEEOdjEngJY54SWPEn0iwyg_M83Mo1CvKllMsPMbpinRQ5R1psQKhRRZVxeYPltpUnkVHVdKkjXZvbJmyjvaFiOVzjKW5OgMIP6Eu6vwg3WY8kn4L-VZM0BJBqIGMCCJ4GuCnQoB-wP27cUTOO6gZCNsNwVM1NzWsd8CPoPpsYVwFWEnvnkdxuqW3T_zDqBVSIveTiCY7tb36GAHYuIa1o9Af976xVSqA",
  "info": "Automatic processing of positives disabled, submit positive to authority manually!",
  "emailSendSuccessful": true,
  "requireManualSendOfPositive": true,
  "qr": "data:image/png;base64,"
}
```

resources.name: Validate Token
resources.description:
## Description
You can either validate a given JWT Token with the .well-known files and the public key or by sending the token as a post request to this endpoint.

## Reponse Codes

- 200 Token is valid
- 410 Token was valid but is expired now
- 400 Invalid token

## Response Body
You can find the description of all fieeld in the Sign Token Request

```
{
  "sub": "043f455a-9cc5-4c7a-8514-143aeccf41eb",
  "aud": "meine-teststation.de",
  "nbf": 1618772358,
  "iss": "http:\/\/localhost:9000",
  "pld": {
    "person": {
      "birthday": "1980-10-01",
      "zip": "832022",
      "country": "de",
      "firstname": "Max",
      "phoneNumber": "08031585858",
      "city": "Rosenheim",
      "sex": "M",
      "idCardNumber": "",
      "street1": "BahnhofstraÃŸe 5",
      "street2": "",
      "email": "test@innfactory.de",
      "lastname": "Mustermann"
    },
    "information": {
      "appData1": {
        "customData": "data"
      },
      "isNegative": true,
      "appData2": {
        "customData2": "data"
      },
      "vaccine": "",
      "isVaccinated": true,
      "testType": "PCR"
    }
  },
  "exp": 1618775958,
  "iat": 1618772358
}
```

resources.name: Decrypt AES encrypted JWT
resources.description:
# Decrypt AES 
We send out the result via mail as an AES encoded string. To decode the AES String to a already validated token you can use this API or decrypt it your self. The AES key and the iv bytes are always:

md5(FirstnameLastnameBirthday)

In the most cases you won't need this API, because third-party systems geht the unencrypted token and can then print the qr code or fetch the PDF as page 2.

## Reponse Codes

- 200 Token is valid
- 410 Token was valid but is expired now
- 400 Invalid token or decryption failed

# Result
The result is are validated JWT token.

resources.name: Generate a PDF Result page from JWT
resources.description:
# PDF
Generates a predefined test result pdf from the JWT which the third-party tool can send out as page 2

# Result
The result is a PDF document which contains the result data human readable in german and english and a signed QR code for use in Tracing Apps.

resources.name: Well Known
resources.description:
Response contains a JWK Remote Key set to validate the token offline by yourself, without the validation endpoint. You should not cache this longer than 12 hours, because every new teststation will get his own key.

**contains all keys** 

You should use this endpoint. The validate token also uses all of these keys to validate the token.

resources.name: Well Known By Audience
resources.description:
Response contains a JWK Remote Key subset set to validate the token offline by yourself, without the validation endpoint. You should not cache this longer than 12 hours, because every new teststation will get his own key.

**filtered by audience domain**
